<p>
<b>Note</b>: The result of the cos<sup>-1</sup> function in the formula is =
in radians.
</p>


<h3>Another method</h3>
<p>
If you know the central angle of the segment (the angle subtended by the se=
gment at the center of the circle) you can use the method
<a href=3D"https://www.mathopenref.com/segmentarea.html">Area of a circular=
 segment given the central angle</a>.
</p>



